HEADWORD: Phosgenite
<hw>Phos"gen*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A rare mineral occurring in tetragonal crystals of a white, yellow,
or grayish color and adamantine luster. It is a chlorocarbonate of
lead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phospham</ent>⟦br⟧
